This paper proposes a method for improving the sample efficiency of reinforcement learning algorithms through imitation learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper specifically focuses on meta-reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning that deals with learning to learn from previous experience. Therefore, the most likely category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of visual observations, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with control problems, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
